				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: first time playing EQ ever<a name="67661"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 6:35 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Chant kiting is when you pull a mob and then run around just stacking dots on it until it falls over dead.
<br />

<br />
Swarm kiting is where you pull a bunch of mobs, get em all nice and neat, then charm one and have it attack another.  Then you run that whole ball of mobs back and they help to beat down your pet.  Right before your pet is dead you invis to break the charm, chant kite your pet till dead, rinse repeat.
<br />
Basically you just let the swarm of mobs do most of the damage for you and you just finish it off for the exp.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
