				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: first time playing EQ ever<a name="67844"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 22 04 3:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>8  - Kelin's Lugubrious Lament
<br />
23 - Selo's Consonant Chain
<br />
34 - Lyssa's Solidarity of Vision
<br />
39 - Solon's Bewitching Bravura
<br />
40 - Syvelian's Anti-Magic Aria
<br />
40 - Sionachie's Dreams
<br />

<br />
Here is your pulling tools at 42.
<br />

<br />
Important thing to remember is that Kelin's Lugubrious Lament dont need a line of sight, just the target. You can see out of line sight with the custom camera view or with Lyssa's Solidarity of Vision. 
<br />

<br />
If you aggro more than one you can split them with Snare/Mez. CHoosing between which one of the 2 is all about timing. What you want is to have a &quot;stream&quot; of mobs constantly going  on your group at the same speed they can manage to kill them. 
<br />

<br />
You can Delay a Whole pack of mob with Charm. When I was able to charm I know I was using it a lot cause if you do it right a Charmed mob = 2+ mob &quot;mezzed&quot; so it buy time while you take control of the crowd. 
<br />

<br />
The most important thing is to know your Crowd Control capacity and play with it. Single pulling is not always the way to go. They will seem to be &quot;single&quot; pulled to the group, but you know that its not the case 0_o 
<br />

<br />
I put Syvelian's Anti-Magic Aria in the pulling tool because thats what I was using to aggro the mobs at that level. Mobs arnt always buffed but when they are it help. Plus having it memed you can remove all the DS that are very nasty sometimes at low level. 
<br />

<br />
You can also use Psalm of Mystic Shielding to protect yourself from snare/root.
<br />

<br />
Something important to notes. Our song look all pretty liek this on paper, but half of the pulling abilities is also related to the environnement. Pathing is a big deal. You will learn eventually some pathing pattern and some mob behaviors that tend to repeat. The trick is to play with those constrains and use them as a tool. You really start to shine at pulling when you use those constraints as a part of your pulling abilities.
<br />

<br />
As for CoM. I dont remember it much, but as far as I know its the same pulling concept than LDoNs. Imho Ldons are a great place to learn how to pull.
<br />

<br />
Hope it help</span></td>
